me documents the significant global connections, circulations, and contributions that African people, ideas, and goods have made throughout the world—from the United States and South Asia to Latin America, Europe, and elsewhere. Through succinct and engaging pieces by scholars, policy makers, activists, and journalists, the volume provides a wholly original view of a continent at the center of global historical processes rather than on the periphery. Global Africa offers fresh, complex, and insightful visions of a continent in flux.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aAfricans. 0aGlobalizationzAfricay21st century. 0aNational characteristics, African. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh  a21st century africa.  aafrican economy.  aafrican foreign relations.  aafrican globalization.  aafrican goods.  aafrican literary traditions.  aafrican people.  aafrican studies.  aafricas global connections.  aangola.  ablack studies.  acharles morris.  acivilized africa.  aenvironmental justice in south africa.  aepidemics in africa.  aglobal black studies.  ahistory of apartheid.  aibn khaldun.  aleymah gbowee.  amwalimu nyerere.  apolitics of africa.  awomen of the sahara.1 aAlegi, Peter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBabou, Cheikh Anta, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aByfield, Judith A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aByfield, Judith, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aCarton, Benedict, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChachage, Chambi, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aClarke, Christa, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 a